		<div id="comment_body_64155413"><p>If proper backups were performed, and proper DR policies were in place, this is about a days worth of restoration work to correct.</p><p>Tops.</p><p>20TB is, as the user below points out, "Not that much" in datacenter terms.  On enterprise scale SAN systems, that much data can be handled in just a few hours.</p><p>If they *DIDN'T* have proper backups, and proper DR policies were *NOT* in place, well...<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.... They get to be the poster child for why you need to do those things!</p></div>
